 Switch

Layman meaning:
A switch is like a power strip for networking.
It connects many computers inside the same network.

Simple example:

 10 computers in an office
 All connected to one switch
  â†’ Now they can talk to each other

IT meaning:

 Switch works inside LAN
 It uses MAC addresses
 It does NOT connect to the internet directly

Example:

 Sharing printer
 Internal file sharing
 Internal application access





